Packages that use AzCategoryId
org.openliberty.openaz.azapi The AzApi package contains the interfaces that must be implemented by a provider. 
org.openliberty.openaz.azapi.constants The purpose of this package is to provide constants and Enums that can be used by the other packages in the project. 
org.openliberty.openaz.azapi.pep The goal of this package is to simplify the creation of Policy Enforcement Points or peps built on top of the azapi package (note that where the class descriptions below are blank, that generally means that the class is primarily used for lower layer non-application facing operations).

Uses of AzCategoryId in org.openliberty.openaz.azapi.constants
 

Classes in org.openliberty.openaz.azapi.constants that implement AzCategoryId
 class AzCategoryIdAction
          This CategoryId indicates that the associated AzEntity or AzAttribute is in the XACML Action Category, AzCategoryIdAction.AZ_CATEGORY_ID_ACTION
 class AzCategoryIdEnvironment
          This CategoryId indicates that the associated AzEntity or AzAttribute is in the XACML Environment Category, AzCategoryIdEnvironment.AZ_CATEGORY_ID_ENVIRONMENT
 class AzCategoryIdObligation
          This CategoryId indicates that the associated AzEntity or AzAttribute is in the XACML Obligation Category, AzCategoryIdObligation.AZ_CATEGORY_ID_OBLIGATION
 class AzCategoryIdResource
          This CategoryId indicates that the associated AzEntity or AzAttribute is in the XACML Resource Category, AzCategoryIdResource.AZ_CATEGORY_ID_RESOURCE
 class AzCategoryIdStatusDetail
          This CategoryId indicates that the associated AzEntity or AzAttribute is in the XACML StatusDetail Category, AzCategoryIdStatusDetail.AZ_CATEGORY_ID_STATUSDETAIL
 class AzCategoryIdSubjectAccess
          AzCategoryIdSubject* objects correspond to the values defined in XACML 2.0 Appendix B.4
 class AzCategoryIdSubjectCodebase
          The AzCategoryIdSubjectCodebase identifier indicates a system entity associated with a local or remote codebase that generated the request.
 class AzCategoryIdSubjectIntermediary
          The AzCategoryIdSubjectIntermediary identifier indicates a system entity through which the access request was passed.
 class AzCategoryIdSubjectRecipient
          The AzCategoryIdSubjectRecipient identifier indicates the system entity that will receive the results of the request (used when it is distinct from the access-subject).
 class AzCategoryIdSubjectRequestingMachine
          The AzCategoryIdSubjectRequestingMachine identifier indicates a system entity associated with the computer that initiated the access request.
